1: Ignore MAC_ENTRY_LOCKED flag during FIND SMALLEST or SCAN commands.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Specifies age intervals are taken into account during FIND SMALLEST or SCAN commands .
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
x0: Don't find entries in the corresponding age interval.
0x: Entries with the corresponding interval are taken into account.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Configures if FIND SMALLEST command or SCAN command cares about ISDX_LIMIT_IDX values or not.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: Disable ISDX_LIMIT_IDX filter (and ignore ISDX_LIMIT_IDX) during SCAN and FIND_SMALLEST commands.
1: Enable ISDX_LIMIT_IDX filter during SCAN and FIND_SMALLEST. Only entries with ISDX_LIMIT_IDX value equal to LRN::MAC_ACCESS_CFG_3.MAC_ENTRY_ISDX_LIMIT_IDX will be found.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Configures if FIND SMALLEST command or SCAN command cares about FID values or not.

It is possible to configure additional FID filters through:
ANA_L2:COMMON:SCAN_FID_CTRL.SCAN_FID_ENA and 
ANA_L2:COMMON:SCAN_FID_CFG.SCAN_FID_VAL
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: Disable FID/VID filters (and ignore FID/VID) during SCAN and FIND_SMALLEST commands.
1: Enable FID/VID filter(s) during SCAN and FIND_SMALLEST. Only entries with FID/VID value equal to LRN::MAC_ACCESS_CFG_0.MAC_ENTRY_FID or optionally also values configured in ANA_L2:COMMON:SCAN_FID_CFG.SCAN_FID_VAL will be found.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Specifies whether ADDR values is don't care or will only affect entries with a specific ADDR value during FIND SMALLEST or SCAN commands (refer also to MAC_ENTRY_ADDR, MAC_ENTRY_ADDR_TYPE and FID_FILTER_ENA / MAC_ENTRY_ADDR).
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: Disable. SCAN and FIND_SMALLEST commands will treat MAC_ENTRY_ADDR and MAC_ENTRY_ADDR_TYPE values as don't care.
1: Enable MAC_ENTRY_ADDR and MAC_ENTRY_ADDR_TYPE filter. SCAN and FIND_SMALLEST commands will only search for entries with Address value corresponding to MAC_ENTRY_ADDR and MAC_ENTRY_ADDR_TYPE taking LRN::SCAN_NEXT_CFG_1.SCAN_ENTRY_ADDR_MASK into account).
