<reg_public_text>:
Configures automated age scan of MAC table. 

This register is replicated for the four age intervals supported. 

Age interval are configured for auto learned entries through:
LRN:COMMON:AUTO_LRN_CFG.AUTO_AGE_INTERVAL

Age intervals are configured for CPU learned entries through:
LRN:COMMON:MAC_ACCESS_CFG_2.MAC_ENTRY_AGE_INTERVAL
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Sets the unit time. Setting UNIT_SIZE to zero effectively disables ageing.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: Disable age scan 
1: 100 us (fastest possible scan is best case 150 us so increase AUTOAGE_PERIOD_VAL to 2)
2: 10 ms
3: 1 s
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Time in units between automatic ageing of an entry.
If otherwise subject to ageing, an inactive entry is removed after between 3*AGE_PERIOD_VAL and 4*AGE_PERIOD_VAL.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: Disabled
n: Age period = n * UNIT_SIZE
