------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if a valid MAC entry has been updated (refreshed), i.e. a write access to the same bucket with the same MAC and VID has occurred. Write '1' to clear this field.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: No entries have been refreshed.
1: An entry has been refreshed.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if a valid MAC entry has been overwritten, i.e. a write access to the same bucket with a changed MAC and/or VID has occurred. Write '1' to clear this field.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: No entries have been replaced.
1: An entry has been replaced.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if a MAC entry has been inserted into an empty MAC table row,column (=bucket). Write '1' to clear this field.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: No entries have been inserted into an empty bucket
1: An entry has been inserted into an empty bucket.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if an CPU learning operation has failed due to hash table depletion (i.e. all entries in a row were locked). Write '1' to clear this field.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: No CPU LEARN operations has failed.
1: A CPU LEARN operation has failed.
------------------------------
